{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2da896c6-e73b-4410-a180-f1c51a4e1692","content":"The template is **technically valid** but has several gaps that should be addressed before publishing to NuGet:\n\n### Missing / Recommended\n\n| Field | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `$schema` | ❌ Missing | Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for editor support |\n| `description` | ❌ Missing | **Important for NuGet discoverability** — users won't know what this template does |\n| `groupIdentity` | ❌ Missing | Recommended so related templates can be grouped (e.g. `MyCompany.WebApi`) |\n| `preferNameDirectory` | ❌ Missing | Usually `true` for project templates |\n\n### Functional Concern\n\nThe `Framework` symbol has no `replaces` property — it won't substitute into project files unless wired up elsewhere (e.g. via a `TargetFramework` replacement in the `.csproj`). Typically you'd add:\n```json\n\"replaces\": \"net9.0\"\n```\n\n### What's Good\n\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `classifications`, `tags` — all present and well-formed.\n- `sourceName` is set for namespace renaming.\n\n**Verdict:** Not quite ready. At minimum, add a `description` and fix the `Framework` symbol's `replaces` before publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"24413a3e-e71e-4aab-819c-107a6b076615","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I can identify:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Best practice to include `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for tooling support.\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet packages so multiple templates can be grouped.\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Useful when multiple versions of a template exist.\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Minor, but good to have.\n5. **`sourceName`** — Present, which is good.\n\n\n6. **`identity`** — Present and looks reasonable.\n7. **`shortName`** — Present.\n8. **`author`** — Present.\n9. **`classifications`** — Present.\n10. **`tags`** — Present with language and type.\n\nThe core required fields are all there: `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, and `author`. However, I'm missing some important additions like `$schema` for editor support, `groupIdentity` for organizing templates on NuGet, and a `description` field which would be valuable for discoverability.\n\nThere's also a functional issue — the `Framework` symbol lacks a `replaces` property, so it won't actually substitute anything in the project files unless that's handled elsewhere in the configuration.","outputTokens":736,"requestId":"9C05:3BE8A6:1D00BDE:207F47A:6A07C08D"},"id":"c4a421ad-e3ed-4263-9fdf-22637bf20eae","timestamp":"2026-05-16T00:55:56.638Z","parentId":"a435232b-6826-4fb2-a624-dc6312a3d788"}
